trans-unit.source: Defines the routing behavior, which is used to configure the destination endpoints, filters and filtering options to be used during routing.

The <xref:System.ServiceModel.Routing.RoutingBehavior> registers all of the run-time components used by the routing service, including the channel initializer, <xref:System.ServiceModel.Routing.SoapProcessingBehavior>, and the <xref:System.ServiceModel.Routing.RoutingExtension>.
Creates a new instance of the <xref href="System.ServiceModel.Routing.RoutingBehavior"></xref> class with the specified routing configuration.

The <xref:System.ServiceModel.Routing.RoutingBehavior> registers all of the run-time components used by the routing service, including the channel initializer, <xref:System.ServiceModel.Routing.SoapProcessingBehavior>, and the <xref:System.ServiceModel.Routing.RoutingExtension>, which uses the specified <xref:System.ServiceModel.Routing.RoutingConfiguration>.
Gets the contract type for the specified <xref href="System.ServiceModel.Description.ContractDescription"></xref>.
The contract description to get the type of.

Implements the <xref href="System.ServiceModel.Description.IServiceBehavior.AddBindingParameters(System.ServiceModel.Description.ServiceDescription,System.ServiceModel.ServiceHostBase,System.Collections.ObjectModel.Collection{System.ServiceModel.Description.ServiceEndpoint},System.ServiceModel.Channels.BindingParameterCollection)"></xref> method to support the behavior.
The service description of the service.
Custom objects to which binding elements have access.

Implements the <xref href="System.ServiceModel.Description.IServiceBehavior.ApplyDispatchBehavior(System.ServiceModel.Description.ServiceDescription,System.ServiceModel.ServiceHostBase)"></xref> method to support the behavior.
The service description of the service.
